A 20-year old man, Happiness Daniel, was yesterday arraigned before an Ikeja Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly attacking Bassey Omo at an Automated Teller Machine (ATM) portal with a knife. Daniel was arraigned before Chief Magistrate Olufunke Sule-Amzat on a two-count charge of stealing and threat to life. Prosecuting Inspector Benson Emuerhi said Daniel committed the offence on June 10 at Allen Avenue, Ikeja. Emuerhi alleged that Daniel also stole a wallet containing First City Monument Bank (FCMB), United Bank for Africa (UBA) and Guarantee Trust Bank (GTB) ATM cards, Police Community Relations Committee (PCRC) identity card, company card and other valuable items valued at N50,000, being property of Jimoh Tunde. Daniel pleaded not guilty. Chief Magistrate Sule-Amzat granted him N100,000 bail, with two sureties in the like sum. The case continues on July 26.